Larva . Head capsule yellow with dark postmentum and broad almost black occipital margin; mentum ( Fig. 5B ) and 4 inner mandibular teeth ( Fig. 5C ) golden-brown. Clypeus ( Fig. 6N ) oval, wider anteriorly with somewhat flared anterolateral lobes; clypeal setae placed near to lateral margin. Inner margin of mandible with one broad lobe near insertion of seta subdentalis and 3 spines near mid-point of mola. Antenna (
Fig. 5I
) with AR 1.2–1.4; 3 rd segment much longer than 2 nd , with conventional wall (not thinned as in other taxa with long 3 rd segment). Ventromental plates 6–17% wider than mentum width. Mensural features as in Table 2 .
